.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Calendar \- NIP\-52 Calendar Events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Calendar;
\&
\&    # Date\-based calendar event (kind 31922)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->date_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqvacation\-2024\*(Aq,
\&        title        => \*(AqSummer Vacation\*(Aq,
\&        content      => \*(AqTwo weeks off\*(Aq,
\&        start        => \*(Aq2024\-07\-01\*(Aq,
\&        end          => \*(Aq2024\-07\-15\*(Aq,
\&        locations    => [\*(AqBeach Resort\*(Aq],
\&        participants => [[$friend_pk, \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq, \*(Aqattendee\*(Aq]],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Time\-based calendar event (kind 31923)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->time_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqstandup\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqDaily Standup\*(Aq,
\&        start      => 1700000000,
\&        end        => 1700003600,
\&        start_tzid => \*(AqAmerica/New_York\*(Aq,
\&        days       => [19675],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Calendar (kind 31924)
\&    my $cal = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->calendar(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqpersonal\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqPersonal Calendar\*(Aq,
\&        events     => [
\&            ["31922:$pk:vacation\-2024", \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # RSVP (kind 31925)
\&    my $rsvp = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->rsvp(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqrsvp\-1\*(Aq,
\&        event_coord  => "31922:$organizer_pk:vacation\-2024",
\&        status       => \*(Aqaccepted\*(Aq,
\&        fb           => \*(Aqbusy\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any calendar event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Calendar\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-52 (Calendar Events). Four addressable event kinds are
used:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBDate\-Based Calendar Event\fR (kind 31922) \- All\-day or multi\-day
events where time and time zone hold no significance.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBTime\-Based Calendar Event\fR (kind 31923) \- Events spanning
between a start time and end time.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBCalendar\fR (kind 31924) \- A collection of calendar events.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBCalendar Event RSVP\fR (kind 31925) \- Attendance response to a
calendar event.
.PP
All four kinds are addressable and deletable per NIP\-09.
.SS "Common tags for calendar events"
.IX Subsection "Common tags for calendar events"
Both date\-based and time\-based calendar events share these tags:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR (required) \- unique identifier
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR (required) \- title of the event
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR (optional) \- brief description
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR (optional) \- URL of an image
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`location\*(C'\fR (optional, repeated) \- location string
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`g\*(C'\fR (optional) \- geohash for searchable location
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR (optional, repeated) \- participant pubkey, relay URL, and role
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR (optional, repeated) \- hashtag
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR (optional, repeated) \- reference URL
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR (repeated) \- reference to kind 31924 calendar
.PP
The deprecated \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR tag is mapped to \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR when parsing if
\&\f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR is not present.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $cal = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmeeting\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqTeam Meeting\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Calendar\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown
arguments. Array fields default to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR defaults to
\&\f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS date_event
.IX Subsection "date_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->date_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        identifier   => $id,                  # required (d tag)
\&        title        => $title,               # required (title tag)
\&        start        => \*(AqYYYY\-MM\-DD\*(Aq,         # required
\&        end          => \*(AqYYYY\-MM\-DD\*(Aq,         # optional
\&        content      => $description,         # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        summary      => $text,                # optional
\&        image        => $url,                 # optional
\&        locations    => [$location],           # optional
\&        geohash      => $geohash,             # optional
\&        participants => [[$pk, $relay, $role]], # optional
\&        hashtags     => [$tag],               # optional
\&        references   => [$url],               # optional
\&        calendars    => [$coord],             # optional (a tags)
\&        created_at   => time(),               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31922 date\-based calendar Net::Nostr::Event. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR date is inclusive and in ISO 8601 format (YYYY\-MM\-DD). The
\&\f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR date is exclusive. If \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR is omitted, the event ends on the
same date as \f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR must be less than \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR if both are
present (enforced by "validate").
.SS time_event
.IX Subsection "time_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->time_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        identifier   => $id,                  # required (d tag)
\&        title        => $title,               # required (title tag)
\&        start        => $unix_timestamp,      # required
\&        end          => $unix_timestamp,      # optional
\&        start_tzid   => \*(AqAmerica/New_York\*(Aq,   # optional (IANA TZ)
\&        end_tzid     => \*(AqAmerica/New_York\*(Aq,   # optional (IANA TZ)
\&        days         => [$day_number],        # required per spec (D tags)
\&        content      => $description,         # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        summary      => $text,                # optional
\&        image        => $url,                 # optional
\&        locations    => [$location],           # optional
\&        geohash      => $geohash,             # optional
\&        participants => [[$pk, $relay, $role]], # optional
\&        hashtags     => [$tag],               # optional
\&        references   => [$url],               # optional
\&        calendars    => [$coord],             # optional (a tags)
\&        created_at   => time(),               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31923 time\-based calendar Net::Nostr::Event. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR timestamp is inclusive (Unix seconds). The \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR timestamp is
exclusive. If \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR is omitted, the event ends instantaneously.
\&\f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR must be less than \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR if both are present (enforced by
"validate"). \f(CW\*(C`days\*(C'\fR are day\-granularity timestamps (\f(CW\*(C`D\*(C'\fR tags)
calculated as \f(CW\*(C`floor(unix_seconds / 86400)\*(C'\fR. The spec requires at
least one \f(CW\*(C`D\*(C'\fR tag (enforced by "validate").
.SS calendar
.IX Subsection "calendar"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->calendar(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,            # required
\&        identifier => $id,                    # required (d tag)
\&        title      => $title,                 # required (title tag)
\&        content    => $description,           # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        events     => [[$coord, $relay]],     # optional (a tags)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31924 calendar Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`events\*(C'\fR is an
arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a calendar event coordinate and
optional relay URL.
.SS rsvp
.IX Subsection "rsvp"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->rsvp(
\&        pubkey             => $hex_pubkey,    # required
\&        identifier         => $id,            # required (d tag)
\&        event_coord        => $coord,         # required (a tag)
\&        status             => \*(Aqaccepted\*(Aq,     # required
\&        event_relay        => $url,           # optional (a tag relay)
\&        event_id           => $eid,           # optional (e tag)
\&        event_id_relay     => $url,           # optional (e tag relay)
\&        fb                 => \*(Aqbusy\*(Aq,         # optional (free/busy)
\&        event_author       => $pk,            # optional (p tag)
\&        event_author_relay => $url,           # optional (p tag relay)
\&        content            => $note,          # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31925 RSVP Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR must be
\&\f(CW\*(C`accepted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`declined\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`tentative\*(C'\fR. The \f(CW\*(C`fb\*(C'\fR tag is
automatically omitted when \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR is \f(CW\*(C`declined\*(C'\fR.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $cal = Net::Nostr::Calendar\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 31922, 31923, 31924, or 31925 event into a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Calendar\*(C'\fR object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
Handles the deprecated \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR tag (mapped to \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR if \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR is
absent).
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Calendar\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-52 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 31922, 31923, 31924, or 31925
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31922/31923 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31922/31923 \f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR is not less than \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR (when \f(CW\*(C`end\*(C'\fR
is present)
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31923 missing \f(CW\*(C`D\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31924 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31925 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31925 \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR is not \f(CW\*(C`accepted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`declined\*(C'\fR, or
\&\f(CW\*(C`tentative\*(C'\fR
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value.
.SS title
.IX Subsection "title"
The calendar event or calendar title.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
The event content. Defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS start
.IX Subsection "start"
The start date (YYYY\-MM\-DD for kind 31922) or Unix timestamp string
(for kind 31923).
.SS end
.IX Subsection "end"
The end date or Unix timestamp string, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS summary
.IX Subsection "summary"
Brief description, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS image
.IX Subsection "image"
Image URL, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS locations
.IX Subsection "locations"
Arrayref of location strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS geohash
.IX Subsection "geohash"
Geohash string, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS participants
.IX Subsection "participants"
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing pubkey, optional relay URL, and
optional role. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS hashtags
.IX Subsection "hashtags"
Arrayref of hashtag strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS references
.IX Subsection "references"
Arrayref of reference URL strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS calendars
.IX Subsection "calendars"
Arrayref of kind 31924 calendar coordinates (from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags in calendar
events). Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS calendar_events
.IX Subsection "calendar_events"
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a calendar event coordinate and
optional relay URL (from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags in calendars). Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS start_tzid
.IX Subsection "start_tzid"
IANA Time Zone Database identifier for the start time (kind 31923 only).
.SS end_tzid
.IX Subsection "end_tzid"
IANA Time Zone Database identifier for the end time (kind 31923 only).
.SS days
.IX Subsection "days"
Arrayref of day\-granularity timestamp strings (\f(CW\*(C`D\*(C'\fR tags, kind 31923
only). Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS event_coord
.IX Subsection "event_coord"
The calendar event coordinate (\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag value, RSVP only).
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
The specific calendar event revision ID (\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag value, RSVP only).
.SS status
.IX Subsection "status"
RSVP status: \f(CW\*(C`accepted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`declined\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`tentative\*(C'\fR.
.SS fb
.IX Subsection "fb"
Free/busy indicator: \f(CW\*(C`free\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`busy\*(C'\fR. Must be omitted or ignored if
\&\f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR is \f(CW\*(C`declined\*(C'\fR.
.SS event_author
.IX Subsection "event_author"
Pubkey of the calendar event author (RSVP only).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-52 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/52.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
